cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.CC

The paper discusses a neurally plausible model of human visual perceptual organization, which suggests that it belongs to the field of neural networks and artificial intelligence (cs.NE and cs.AI). The use of hyperstrings, a distributed representation, and transparallel information processing also suggest that it could be related to machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the mention of classical computing with quantum power suggests that it could also be related to quantum computing (cs.CC).
